# Chapter 5: Feature Engineering

## Introduction

Feature Engineering is the process of creating, selecting, and transforming features that help machine learning models learn better patterns from data.

Good features often improve model performance more than changing algorithms.

Many data scientists consider feature engineering one of the most important skills in machine learning.

---

# What is a Feature?

A feature is an input variable used by a machine learning model.

Example:

Insurance Dataset

Features:

* Age
* BMI
* Children
* Smoker Status

Target:

* Insurance Charges

The model uses the features to predict the target.

---

# Why Feature Engineering is Important

Raw data is not always useful.

Feature engineering transforms raw data into meaningful information.

Better Features

↓

Better Learning

↓

Better Predictions

---

